Description: A used Les Paul style guitar, Made by Gibson Baldwin for their education series. Why buy a new, expensive guitar if you're not sure if this is the thing for you? You can buy a guitar for several hundred dollars, then have it collecting dust in a few months. That's why I bought this model, and found out quickly that I didn't have what it took to be the next Jimi Hendrix. So I'm glad I didn't spend a ton of money on it. Don't get me wrong, it will still scream like its big brothers, but at a fraction of the cost. For you, for your kid, for your Grandma! For whoever! It was bought around 1997, and it has a few scuffs and chips. It's missing both knobs for volume and tone. You can get them at any music store. It comes with a mini amp, powered by a 9-volt battery. Or you can get a 9-volt adapter and plug it into the wall. It also has a 10 foot cord, and a nice guitar stand. I have shipping set at $40, but if you live close to Monmouth County, New Jersey, we can meet up and you can save the shipping! Shipping to the US only, no exceptions!
Title: Maestro by Gibson Electric Guitar Starter Pack Vintage Sunburst w/Amp Les Paul
